article.headline: Morehead State 65, Samford 60
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Ricky Minard and Chez Marks each scored 19 points lead Morehead State to a 65-60 victory over Samford Thursday night. Minard was 7-of-19 from the field and grabbed seven rebounds for the Eagles (8-8, 3-2 Ohio Valley Conference), while Marks hit 8 of 17. Chad McKnight and Craig Lewis also reached double figures, scoring 12 and 10, respectively. Samford (8-8, 3-2) had a 47-44 lead with 8:35 remaining, when Marks hit three back-to-back 3-pointers topped with a layup, putting the Eagles ahead 55-47. The Bulldogs answered with an 11-3 run, driven by 3-pointers from Tyson Dorsey and Robert Merritt, tying the game again at 58-all. Craig Lewis hit four free throws in the final minute of the game, sealing the victory for Morehead State. Dorsey led the Bulldogs with 29 points, the only double figures for Samford. The Eagles outrebounded Samford 35-27, and scored 25 points off the Bulldogs' 18 turnovers.
